data.reddit:
27 Y.O. White male apx 160 lbs, 5’11”. Pretty fit, work out 5 days a week, ran a marathon just north of 4 hours in June. 

Been suffering from sort of colicky upper left abdominal pain and left middle back pain with a little numb spot/pins and needles directly left of T-7/T8 for about 6 months now. Those are the only symptoms. No GI issues, Jaundice, I otherwise feel great. So far the workup has been negative. I’ve had the following which have all come up normal:

-Lipase & Amylase x2
-Liver panel x2
-Fasting Glucose 
- Contrast enhanced Helical CT Abd./Plvs
- Thoracic MRI
-10ish Chiropractor visits
- Upper Endoscopy

I have a diagnosed anxiety disorder, as does my mother, sister, several aunts. At this point I’m wondering if this is all “In my head”. Of course I’ve consulted Dr. Google (Terrible idea) with the location of my  symptoms and I’ve got it in my head that I have pancreatic cancer. I know it’s HIGHLY unlikely for my age group and I don’t smoke, it doesn’t run in my family, I don’t really have any other risk factors. But I can’t help but be concerned.

So basically, Title. Is my fear of PC irrational, or do I need to continue to fight with Doctors to order more tests?
